description:
Almond frozen dessert with a salted caramel swirl & pieces of almond brittle. Deliciously nutty and a little crunchy with a swirl of salty caramel running through its heart, this Non-Dairy frozen dessert is a true vegan charmer.

Creamy. Crunchy. A little nutty. If Caramel Almond Brittle Non-Dairy were a human, not a flavor, it'd be the most likeable person in the room, capable of leaving fellow partygoers swooning in its wake. And that's where this flavor shines the brightest. Yup, it's a non-dairy, certified-vegan, lactose-free frozen dessert made with almond milk. Our almond milk provides a creamy, dreamy blank canvas for the delights that are the Ben & Jerry's Non-Dairy line. And thanks to our Flavor Gurus' whiz-bang wizardry in the Flavor Lab, Caramel Almond Brittle Non-Dairy is a flavor that vegans and dairy-lovers alike really dig. And dig into.

And just because it's part of our Non-Dairy line doesn't mean we don't put the full weight of Ben & Jerry's values behind it, so Caramel Almond Brittle Non-Dairy is made with non-GMO sourced ingredients and features sugar and vanilla farmed by Fairtrade certified producers. Oh, and it's 100% vegan certified, packed in a responsibly sourced container—and still totally euphoric.

description: Cherry frozen dessert with cherries and fudge flakes. This flavor is our tribute to guitarist Jerry Garcia fans everywhere, and it all started with a piece of fan mail.Back in the day, before smart phones and social media, our fans spoke to us via handwritten notes pinned to the bulletin boards at our Scoop Shops. Sometime in 1986, one such fan mailed a postcard to our main office in Burlington, Vermont, suggesting this now-iconic flavor. Ice cream meets great guitar solos? We loved the idea, and Ben immediately got to work concocting it. Cherry Garcia debuted in 1987 and quickly became one of our top three most popular flavors. But just as every good musician has to evolve, Ben & Jerry's does, too. So in answer to queries from all of those air-guitar heroes who wanted a dairy-less option, we decided it was time to create a dairy-free, 100% vegan take on Cherry Garcia. It's made with smooth and creamy almond milk, which is the perfect blank canvas for the cherries and fudge flakes we pack into this pint. Here's hoping it inspires at least a few soulful guitar riffs powered by Non-Dairy goodness.Like all of our flavors, Cherry Garcia Non-Dairy is made with non-GMO-sourced ingredients, and Fairtrade certified cocoa, sugar, and vanilla. If that's not enough, we went one step further to gain 100% vegan certification. Vegans, rejoice! All that flavor is wrapped in responsibly sourced packaging so you can feel good about what's in your freezer.
title: Ben & Jerry's Non Dairy Cherry Garcia - 16 fl oz

description: Natural and artificial flavor added. We go to extremes to make our ice cream. We search the world for the ingredients. Our cocoa beans come from the Ivory Coast of Africa. All of these exotic ingredients end up in our hometown of Brenham, Texas (population 10,000). Why do we go to all this trouble? Because using the finest ingredients is the only way to make the best ice cream. And the best ice cream in the country is what folks expect from Blue Bell. description: Talenti makes delicious, indulgent gelatos and sorbettos with special ingredients, crafted just for you. description: Talenti makes delicious, indulgent gelatos and sorbettos with special ingredients, crafted just for you. We start with fresh milk and pure cane sugar–absolutely never high-fructose corn syrup. We then add the finest ingredients sourced from all around the world and slow cook the gelato to slightly caramelize the flavors for a one-of-a-kind tasting experience. And because we don't inject extra air into the product, you'll enjoy a richer flavor with a denser consistency. Even better, our treats are milk-based rather than cream-based, so they are lower in fat than regular ice cream while tasting just as decadent. We package it in clear, BPA-free jars to keep it fresh and to give you a peek inside. When you're done, recycle or reuse the jar anyway you like. Try all our 42 flavors and discover your favorite! Basic isn't boring with Talenti Belgian Chocolate gelato. We blend hand-melted, imported Belgian chocolate until smooth with fresh milk, cream, eggs and a dash of vanilla. description: Talenti makes delicious, indulgent gelatos and sorbettos with special ingredients, crafted just for you. New Talenti Cinnamon Peach Biscuit gelato is like eating an entire picnic on a hot summer day by the spoonful. Like all our gelatos, we start with fresh milk and real cane sugar–absolutely never high-fructose corn syrup. We then add the finest ingredients sourced from all around the world, and slow cook the gelato to slightly caramelize the flavors for a one-of-a-kind tasting experience. For this flavor, we infuse the cinnamon sugar base by steeping real cinnamon sticks in the milk and cream. Next, we swirl peach butter through the cinnamon sugar base. Peach butter, like all fruit butters, combines the essence of real fruit with the silky texture of a sauce. Finally, we sprinkle biscuit cookie pieces throughout the gelato to add a buttery crunch to every bite. And because we don't add extra air into the product, you'll enjoy a richer flavor with a denser consistency. Even better, our treats are milk-based rather than cream-based, so they are lower in fat. We package it in clear, BPA-free jars to keep it fresh and to give you a peek inside. When you're done, recycle or reuse the clear jar anyway you like. Try all our 40 flavors and discover your favorite!

description:

The Story of Coolhaus: In 2008, while working our other jobs in design and real estate, we started making ice cream and cookies from scratch in our kitchen with local, sustainably sourced & unique ingredients. We named the combinations after architects we loved to support our community. Soon after, we bought a postal van and converted it into an ice cream truck. Popularity grew quickly, and now we have a national fleet, storefronts, and our handmade sandwiches available pre-packed like the one you're holding right now. Even though we've grown, nothing has changed about our sourcing, making things from scratch, innovating our favorite flavor combinations, or our punny architectural names. description: 12 thick ice cream sandwiches. 25% more ice cream than competing ice cream sandwiches. Thick and creamy real ice cream since 1925. Creamy. Smooth. It All Began in 1925: Way back in 1925, Casper Merrill took the milk and cream from the family milk cows and made the first original Ice Cream Casco Nut Sundae on a Stick. He made those first nut sundaes in a ten-gallon milk can and sold them at the local 4th of July celebration. Soon after, Casper developed his original FatBoy Ice Cream Sandwich, a much larger than usual ice cream novelty. Everyone who tried those first Casco Nut Sundaes and FatBoy Ice Cream Sandwiches enjoyed them so much they wanted more. So, Casper began making them on a large scale and soon people all over the entire Intermountain West were enjoying them. The original ingredients and recipe have changed very little over the years. Today, folks all across the country are eating and enjoying Casco Nut Sundaes and FatBoy Ice Cream Sandwiches just as much as those who enjoyed the first ones during the 4th of July celebration of 1925. Manufactured with pride.
